RTOS_CMSISOS_RTOS001 App

NOTE: URIs given in tables below are for App developer use. App developer can make use of these URIs to create top level apps by consuming this app.

Virtual Signals

None.

Provided Parameters

Name URI Description Access Mode
RTOS Selection rtos001_erwrtosselection Selects the specific RTOS to be used.
Currently only RTX is supported.		R/W
Memory Pools rtos001_erwmempool Enables support for Memory Pools.
CMSIS RTOS supports fixed sized memory pools.
When the memory pool is initialized, the RTX kernel handles memory requests by allocating a block of memory from the memory pool. 		R/W
Mail Queues rtos001_erwmailq Enables support for Mail Queues.
A mail is a memory block that is send to a thread or interrupt service routine. 		R/W
Message Queues rtos001_erwmsgq Enables support for Message Queues.
A message can be a integer or pointer value that is send to a thread or ISR.		R/W
Generic Wait Function rtos001_erwoswait Enables support for the generic wait function osWait.
RTX RTOS does not support this feature.		R
Maximum Signal Flags rtos001_irwsignals Configures the maximum Signal Flags available per thread.
The CMSIS-RTOS API may support a variable number of signal flags.
For RTX RTOS this parameter is not configurable; fixed value of 16 Signal Flags per thread is used.		R
Maximum Semaphore Resources rtos001_irwsemaphores Configures the maximum index count for a Semaphore.
It should be within the range of 1 to 65535. 		R
Timer Tick value in us rtos001_irwtick This allows user to enter timer tick value in us. R/W

Maximum Number of concurrent running threads rtos001_irwtaskcnt This allows user to enter maximum number of threads that will run at the same time R/W
Number of threads with user-provided stack size rtos001_irwpricnt This allows user to enter the number of threads with user-provided stack size R/W
Number of threads with default stack size rtos001_irdefaultcnt This is the difference between number of concurrent running threads and number of threads with user provided stack size.This is non-editable. R
Privileged Mode rtos001_erwrunpriv This allows to run all threads in privileged mode. R/W
Default stack size for threads in bytes rtos001_irwstksize This allows user to enter default stack size for threads. R/W
Total stack size for threads with user-provided stack size in bytes rtos001_irwprivstksize This allows user to enter the combined stack size for threads with user-provided stack size.This field will be editable only when user enters non zero value for "Number of threads with user-provided stack size" R/W
Stack checking code rtos001_erwstkcheck This allows to includes the stack checking code for stack overflow R/W
User timer Thread stack size in bytes rtos001_irwtimerstksize This allows user to enter stack size for timer thread in bytes [64 - 4096].This field will be editable only when user timer is enabled. R/W
Total Stack Requirement rtos001_irtotalstksize This informs total stack requirement.non-editable field R
Round Robin Thread Switching rtos001_erwrndrobin This allows user to enable round robin thread switching R/W
Round-Robin Timeout in Ticks rtos001_irwrobintout This allows user to enter how long a thread will execute before a thread switch R/W
Maximum Number of entries in ISR FIFO Queue rtos001_irwfifosz This allows user to enter maximum number of ISR requests that can be buffered in FIFO Queue R/W
Maximum Number of system mutexes rtos001_irwmutxes This allows to enter maximum number system mutexes that are used to protect the arm standard runtime library R/W
Enable user timers rtos001_erwtimers TThis is to enable user timers R/W
Timer Thread Priority rtos001_erwtimerprio This allows user to enter priority for the timer thread. R/W
Maximum Number of concurrent callbacks rtos001_irwtimercbqsize This allows user to enter maximum number of concurrent callbacks that can be queued R/W
User defined function for Idle demon rtos001_idledemon This allows user to enter the name of the function that is to be executed when no thread runs. R/W
User defined function for os error rtos001_oserror This allows user to enter the name of the function that is to be executed on os error. R/W
